    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.24-27_0001" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Author's Club seal, including a banner</figDesc>
                        <p>AC <!--the following on a figure of a banner as part of the seal-->CEDIT ENSIS CALAMO</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE,
                        <lb/>
                    VICTORIA 3160 (6 LINES)
                        <lb/>
                    TELEGRAMS "AZYRITES, LONDON."
                
                    AUTHOR'S CLUB,
                        <lb/>
                    2,WHITEHALL COURT,
                        <lb/>
                    S.W.1.</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Aug 5. 24</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My Dear Neihardt-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>The cover design, end sheets, title page and 14 initial letters are done and shall go forward to Latham in a day or so. I enclose a couple of the discarded initial letters to let you in on the treatment I am using. <unclear>Burn Em</unclear>.</p>
                    
                <p>I shall go at the full page illustrations next and do them in an order which will scatter them more or less evenly thru<sic>through</sic> the book so that if I don't get all 14 finished the thing will be more or less satisfactory anyway. My health has been a 
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.24-27_0002"/>
                    
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Author's Club seal, including a banner</figDesc>
                        <p>AC <!--the following on a figure of a banner as part of the seal-->CEDIT ENSIS CALAMO</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                        <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE,
                            <lb/>
                        VICTORIA 3160 (6 LINES)
                            <lb/>
                        TELEGRAMS "AZYRITES, LONDON."
                    
                        AUTHOR'S CLUB,
                            <lb/>
                        2,WHITEHALL COURT,
                            <lb/>
                        S.W.1.</hi>
                </fw>
                    
                    mess here in Eng. and I'm rusty at pen and ink so it makes quite a task to do the job. you and Mac. have put up to me. But it will be done gladly if at all. Just now I feel fine. The family is "parked" in North England for a month and I can get exercise regularly <unclear>sculling</unclear> on The Thames.</p>
                    
                <p>But I've 12 canvases of my own each 10x8 ft and 8 of Mrs <unclear>Brangesyus</unclear>, which I am laying in and pushing as far as I can, The latter are 18x30 ft each so like the buck rabbit "I too have not been idle.</p>
             
                <p>Otherwise everything's lovely.
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.24-27_0003"/>     
                    <fw type="curatorial">26</fw>
                    
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Author's Club seal, including a banner</figDesc>
                        <p>AC <!--the following on a figure of a banner as part of the seal-->CEDIT ENSIS CALAMO</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE,
                        <lb/>
                    VICTORIA 3160 (6 LINES)
                        <lb/>
                    TELEGRAMS "AZYRITES, LONDON."
                    
                    AUTHOR'S CLUB,
                        <lb/>
                    2,WHITEHALL COURT,
                        <lb/>
                    S.W.1.</hi>
                </fw>
                    
                    If you have any photos or drawings of the soldiers of the Indian Wars guns, costumes, accoutrament saddles etc x43. shoot some over please. I've got loads of data at home but my memory will not supply data for a Colts Navy revolver or Mc Lellan saddle.</p>
                    
                <p>Don't go to a lot of trouble just shoot. Time is of the essence of the contract.</p>
                    
                <p>Now I'm going home and get a little much needed rest &#8212; or much little needed rest &#8212; I don't care which.</p>
                    
                <p>And, bye the drinks, if
                    
                  <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.24-27_0004"/>
                    
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Author's Club seal, including a banner</figDesc>
                        <p>AC <!--the following on a figure of a banner as part of a seal-->CEDIT ENSIS CALAMO</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEPHONE,
                        <lb/>
                    VICTORIA 3160 (6 LINES)
                        <lb/>
                    TELEGRAMS "AZYRITES, LONDON."
                        
                    AUTHOR'S CLUB,
                        <lb/>
                    2,WHITEHALL COURT,
                        <lb/>
                    S.W.1</hi>
                </fw>
                    
                    you know anything about the back end of a chuck wagon such as was used by the <unclear>cow men</unclear> about 1868 or thereabouts let me in on it. I'm filling a lot of canvas with one of those wagons and don't know much about em. Would it be a Red River Cart?</p>
               
                <p>Thanks awfully old chap.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours respectfully</salute>
                    
                    <signed>True.</signed>
                
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A man's head in profile, wearing glasses, his hand, holding an umbrella, and his foot</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
